                <h1>Construction never stops: Duke breaks ground on new alumni building</h1>
                
                                    <figure class="dom-art-container my-4">
                                                    <img src="https://snworksceo.imgix.net/dtc/621be3c8-2fb6-42b5-a5b5-05dbbc773bd9.sized-1000x1000.jpg?w=1000" alt="&lt;p&gt;The&#x20;Karsh&#x20;Alumni&#x20;and&#x20;Visitor&#x2019;s&#x20;Center&#x20;is&#x20;set&#x20;to&#x20;open&#x20;in&#x20;the&#x20;summer&#x20;of&#x20;2019.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;" class="w-100">
                                                <div class="domphoto-caption mt-2 text-left text-md-right">
                            <p>The Karsh Alumni and Visitor’s Center is set to open in the summer of 2019.</p>

                            
                        </div>
                    </figure>
                
                                    <div class="row  mt-4 mb-0 mb-md-4">
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                            <aside class="author-name">
                                    
    
                                    
            By <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/vir-patel">Vir Patel</a>
                                    
                                <div class="mt-1">
                                    <span class="can-localize">July 14, 2017 | 7:06am EDT</span>
                                </div>
                            </aside>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6 text-left text-md-right d-print-none">
                            <ul class="social-links list-unsyled list-inline mt-4 mt-md-0">
